The paper deals with the visualization of arrangements of pseudolines, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also mentions applications in graph theory (cs.DM), specifically in distance-preserving embeddings into hypercubes, and in sorting networks. The paper discusses the properties of weak outerplanar pseudoline arrangements, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT) and combinatorial geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions the use of pseudoline arrangements to model learning spaces (cs.SI) and the use of force-directed methods for schematizing systems of curves (which is a topic in graph drawing, cs.DS).
